      "content": "To repot your fiddle leaf fig safely, you need a potting mix that is airy and well-draining, specifically formulated for houseplants or a custom blend of peat moss, perlite, and pumice. Avoid heavy garden soil, as it will suffocate the roots and cause root rot.\n\nWhen repotting, do not fill the new pot completely; add soil only about an inch below the rim to give the roots room to expand. Gently loosen the root ball and remove the old soil carefully, then trim any mushy or dead roots with clean shears before placing the plant in fresh soil. Water lightly afterward and place it in a bright spot with indirect light to help it adjust without shock.",
